# Exclude tripwire-negative fixtures from OpenSSF Scorecard's
# Pinned-Dependencies scan. These files INTENTIONALLY contain `curl | bash`
# and `npm install` so the read-only tripwire (scripts/check-read-only.sh)
# can verify it rejects them. They are bait the tripwire eats, not executed
# code; "pinning" them would defeat their purpose.
#
# Scorecard honors export-ignore only when its action is run with the
# `file_mode: git` input — that's set in .github/workflows/scorecard.yml.
tests/check-read-only/should_fail/**  export-ignore
